    "Although DIRTY is trained on a relatively large dataset, it is still not large enough to cope with the multitudinous code snippets.",
    "It is difficult for DIRTY to handle cases where code contexts never appear in the training set.",
    "For example, regarding MVR, DIRTY performs best on the dataset Coreutils.",
    "This is because the training set contains the corresponding source code and decompiler output.",
    "(ii) The alignment makes DIRTY optimize only partial variable names, and the ignored variable names can hinder the comprehensibility of the decompiler output."
